CatDescriptText: Mr. Edward Anderson, 2837 Wylie Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 23, 1957, pg. 10 with question: "Do you think Negroes in Pittsburgh use their economic power wisely?" answer reads: "I say that Negroes should do more than what they do for the reason of building and taking care of the needs of our race. Some times they do not do enough."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Edward Anderson wearing hat, dark necktie, and light colored trench coat, standing on sidewalk with car and buildings in background
